table.name: wp_ngg_gallery
table.column: Brownies with Cadbury\'s soft toffee dairy milk bars baked in.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Halfway through construction, yes it required nearly six chocolate bars to cover.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: I cheated and used brownie Mix this time.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Yeah, this is what\'s on there, had two left over, whatever will I do with them?

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: The light bits are the Cadbury\'s chocolate and toffee.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: All the things we came away with. Not pictured: two swag bags, well used, and a framed print.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: The pins are for Corset Inspector and Tesla Rangers. We talked a long time to who must have been Kaja Foglio, who was very nice and personable, although she kept reminding us we could read the whole thing online. (You can read the whole series here): http://www.girlgeniusonline.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Completely out of money by the time we got to this booth, but I picked up a card because I liked the concept: http://battlepug.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: This was a free handout. People had lots of them, but I didn\'t want to presume. Pretty cute. http://buttersafe.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: The first person we talked to was Scott Kurtz, stationed with Kris Straub. Taylor got his book signed and sketched, and I got this one. To feel like I was participating http://chainsawsuit.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Upon reading, I am sure I will know what this is all about.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: I was interested in a book called Carry On Carrion: A Crow Funeral, but Taylor fell in love with a drawing of a jackalope and bought the original. We got the book to go along with it. http://www.reidpsaltis.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: A collection of one-off comics about whatever the artist thought of when they heard \"Bear fight.\" http://www.banneryearpress.com/bearfight/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: I loved the black and white style of these comics, which are almost to the point of being combined into a trade. One of the friendliest signers there. http://www.webcomicsnation.com/skorpen/moths/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Of course we were going to get Axe Cop. The artist was on his cellphone the whole time, but I think this was just unfortunate timing. http://axecop.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: This guy was wearing a costume. I should have taken a picture then. Excited about the artwork in this one, which is really old-school. http://www.unemployedman.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: After Taylor threatened to punch Scott Kurtz for giving him the PAX pox two years ago, he was still nice enough to sign and sketch this greatest hits collection. http://www.pvponline.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Considering that his comic has been optioned for a movie, Richard Starkings was certainly gracious. http://www.hipflask.com/

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Look at the sketches he drew!

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: So much artistry. Really, people behind us were getting bored.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: We talked about the Portland rain. He said \"I\'m from England, where we invented the weather.\"

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: I was trying to not look at camera.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: At this bar, the challenge was to combine two random mixed drinks.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: The women we challenged to Never Ever. I won, having a good quarter glass of beer when everyone else was dry

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Talking to our head of house.

table.name: wp_ngg_pictures
table.column: Me at 14 in a kimono my grandparents bought on a mission in Japan.
